<br>
Furthermore, you should know that toe to toe combat is a poor strategy in EQ for soloing. Consequently, (untwinked) melee-only classes generally do quite poorly. Since you're comparing to Paladins, you should know that they are significantly better soloists than Monks during the middle levels because they have easier access to better equipment (and 2-handed weapons are generally better than dual wield in that level range), and have the ability to root MOBS and heal themselves during battle when things go poorly. In the early days of the game, Monks were the better soloists at all levels, but Paladins have received massive enhancements, and are now very good through the mid levels. At high levels, Monks probably still have the advantage at soloing - but not where you are now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=phungkuu>Phung Kuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/8/02 10:59:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Funny... thread.<br>
