<br>
The classes which are most successful are those that kill from a distance, or that can make their opponents run in fear while being damaged. <br>
<br>
Monks don't have many options. You have no meaningful ranged attacks, and your fear abilities are limited (Instill Doubt/Intimidation). That's about it. In other words, Monks are not a great choice for the soloist. Being an Iksar helps considerably, since you get an AC/Damage Mitigation bonus and faster regeneration, but the truth is that Monks are now one of the worst soloist classes in the game...unless you twink. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhaeppwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haeppwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/9/02 2:31:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing</span><hr size=1> hmmm... the fact that as you say toe to toe combat is not effective is shaky at best... I've soloed my way pretty much all the way through to 49... about to ding 50 on my iksar monk. When I started off &quot;twinked&quot; I had a CCS which is debatably worse than LockJaw's no haste and only 1 CoT for a weapon using fist for offhand... I did however have 6/65 rings... but let me tell you I have NEVER soloed in any way beside standing and beating the shit out of mobs... whether bandits in PC orcs in CC mutants in Echo or as of now Umberbulks in Echo again... I would suggest going to the moon again and hunting the top floor of Echo... with a little better gear you could solo mutants as long as they aren't named and people are always lookin for a monk puller in their grps there... as soon as you hit 30 or so... (I went at 28 with a prtner until 30) go to CC and hunt Orc Miners and with a little better gear than you have Watchmen as well... stay away from casters and Foremen... you can do CC for quite some time... I 